The paper deals with compressed sensing and sparse signal recovery, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The use of restricted isometry property (RIC) is also a common technique in compressed sensing, which further supports the likelihood of the paper belonging to these sub-categories.
